Increasing attention needs to be paid to detrimental impacts of commercial activities, especially mineral extraction, and to a lesser extent the disruptive removal of specimens from their natural environments and scientific over-sampling as well as unintentional and intentional damage sampling on vent ecosystems (
Vrijenhoek 2010
; 
Van Dover 2011
, 2014; 

Keaveney 
et al.
2016

; 

Van Dover 
et al.
2016

). Protection and future preservation of biological communities of the unique hydrothermal environments require knowledge of the biodiversity and connectivity of associated species, together with cooperation, effective deep-sea resource management and policy at national and international levels.
